mentary School where Andrea, his girlfriend, worked. After he arrived at the elementary school, which was not in session at the time, he shot and killed Mary Alicia Shanks, 56, and shot Mary Snedeker, 52, nonfatally. He left the school and allegedly shot Chad Johansen, 26 nonfatally. He then turned the gun on himself, but did not die as a result.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.wcax.com/story/5324836/essex-shooting-rampage |title = Essex Shooting Rampage |website = www.wcax.com |access-date = April 21, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160805082746/http://www.wcax.com/story/5324836/essex-shooting-rampage |archivedate = August 5, 2016 |df = mdy-all }}</ref> Williams was sentenced to life in prison without parole in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://law.justia.com/cases/vermont/supreme-court/2010/op2008-469.html|title=State v. Williams|website=Justia Law|accessdate=May 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|August 30, 2006}}\n|{{sort|Hillsborough, North Carolina}}\n|1\n|2\n|After shooting and killing his father, 18-year old teenager Alvaro Castillo went to his [[Orange High School (North Carolina)|high school]] where he wounded two students. He was reportedly obsessed with the [[Columbine shootings]] and had written an email to the current Columbine high school principal before committing his own crime.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/nation/2006-08-31-school-shooting_x.htm |title = North Carolina Shooting Suspect Obsessed with Columbine |work = [[USA Today]] |date = August 31, 2006 }}</ref> he was sentenced to life without parole.<ref>{{cite web|author=By\u00a0 Beth Karas CNN/ In Session |url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/CRIME/08/21/north.carolina.castillo.trial/index.html |title=Man obsessed with Columbine convicted of murder |publisher=CNN.com |date= |accessdate=2019-06-06}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|September 2, 2006}}\n|{{sort|Shepherdstown, West Virginia}}\n|3<ref name=\":1\" group=\"n\" />\n|0\n|49-year-old Douglas W. Penningt