 arguing at one of Cardozo's entrances.  The fight climaxed when Eugene pulled out a handgun and shot his classmate in the leg.  The shooting was captured on the school's surveillance system and witnesses said they heard as many as seven shots.<ref>http://www.columbine-angels.com/School_Violence_2006-2007.htm</ref><ref>https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/opinions/2006/09/23/cardozo-high-school-iii-span-classbankheadthree-shootings-since-1995-speak-to-lessons-ignoredspan/53fbca09-c4c7-4259-9555-1cebab1d2af7/</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|September 27, 2006}}\n|{{sort|Bailey, Colorado}}\n|2<ref name=\":1\" group=\"n\" />\n|0\n|[[Platte Canyon High School hostage crisis]]: 53-year-old drifter, Duane Roger Morrison, walked into [[Platte Canyon High School]] and took six girls hostage. During the ensuing siege, Morrison sexually assaulted all of the girls. When a SWAT team stormed the classroom, Morrison killed 16-year-old Emily Keyes, then took his own life after being shot and wounded by police.<ref>{{cite news |url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=R0MgAAAAIBAJ&pg=6945,3589485 |title = Killer sexually assaulted schoolgirls |work = [[Sarasota Herald-Tribune]] (Sarasota, Florida) |date = September 29, 2006 |page = 7A |first = Catherine |last = Tsai }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|September 29, 2006}}\n|{{sort|Cazenovia, Wisconsin}}\n|1\n|0\n|[[Weston High School shooting]]: At around 8&nbsp;a.m., 15-year-old freshman, Eric Hainstock, entered [[Weston High School (Cazenovia, Wisconsin)|Weston High School]]. He aimed a 20-gauge shotgun at social studies teacher, Chuck Keller, before it was wrestled from him by school custodian, Dave Thompson. Hainstock then shot 49-year-old high school principal, John Alfred Klang, with a .22 caliber revolver. Klang died later that afternoon.{{sfn|Lebrun|2008|p=181}}<ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.semissourian.com/story/1170663.html |title = Neighbor: Teen held in shooting bragged about getting into trouble |work = [[Southeast Missourian]] (Cape Gir