led at [[Bellaire High School (Texas)|Bellaire High School]]. a 16-year-old student was arrested and charged with manslaughter.<ref>https://www.kwtx.com/content/news/Student-shot-at-Texas-high-school-dies-suspect-still-at-large-566989851.html</ref><ref>https://www.khou.com/article/news/crime/bellaire-high-school-shooting-suspect-charged-with-manslaughter/285-594a3ef4-4280-45f2-b548-dafe640e5ee6</ref>\n|-\n| January 14, 2020\n| [[Fort Worth, Texas]]\n|0\n|2\n|An adult male and a 10-year-old child were injured at North Crowley Ninth Grade Campus after a youth basketball game.<ref>https://www.nbcdfw.com/news/local/1-critically-injured-in-shooting-after-youth-basketball-game/2294920/</ref><ref>https://www.wfaa.com/article/news/local/1-person-shot-at-parking-lot-of-school-campus-in-fort-worth-police-say/287-1bc57cb9-271c-4a57-bbfc-6fb21b9c4009</ref>\n|-santa\n| January 23, 2020\n| [[Oxnard, California]]\n|0\n|1\n|<ref>https://www.vcstar.com/story/news/local/communities/oxnard/2020/01/25/oxnard-shooting-mcauliffe-school-stray-bullet-aftermath/4566324002/</ref>\n|-\n| February 3, 2020\n| [[Commerce, Texas]]\n|2\n|1\n|Jacques Dshawn Smith, 21, gained access to Pride Rock Residence hall at [[Texas A&M University\u2013Commerce]], where he is suspected of shooting his ex-girlfriend Abbaney Matts, 20, and her sister Deja Matts, 19, to death. Abbaney's 2-year-old son was also injured during the shooting.<ref>https://www.dallasnews.com/news/education/2020/02/10/student-safety-well-being-in-focus-following-deadly-shooting-at-a-texas-university/</ref><ref>https://www.dallasnews.com/news/2020/02/04/police-dorm-residents-call-led-to-discovery-of-sisters-fatal-shooting-at-texas-am-university-commerce/</ref>\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n<references group=\"n\" />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of school shootings in the United States by death toll]]\n* [[List of school-related attacks]]\n* [[Mass shootings in the United States]]\n*[[List of unsuccessful attacks related to schools]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n\n* {{cite web|url = http://cjonline.com/stories/061102/kan_abbeyshooting.shtml |title = 3 die in Missouri abbey shooting {{!}} CJOnline.com |last = Breaux |first = By Kia Shant'e |website = cjonline.com |access-date = November 28, 2016 }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=WYDQwDvXz9MC&printsec=frontcover |title = Inside the Mind of a Teen Killer |year = 2009 |last = Chalmers |first = Phil |publisher = [[Thomas Nelson (publisher)|Thomas Nelson]] |location = [[Nashville, Tennessee]] |edition = illustrated |isbn = 978-1-59555-152-8 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Crews |first = Gordon A. |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=mnWBCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover |title = Critical Examinations of School Violence and Disturbance in K-12 Education |year = 2016 |publisher = Information Science Reference |location = [[Hershey, Pennsylvania]] |isbn = 978-1-4666-9935-9 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=0a_zPAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover |title = The Murder Book: Examining Homicide |year = 2008 |last = Davies |first = Kim |publisher = Pearson [[Prentice Hall]] |location = [[Upper Saddle River, New Jersey]] |edition = illustrated |isbn = 978-0-13-172401-3 |ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book |last = Dixon |first = David |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=UeaN0-Ra64oC&printsec=frontcover |title = Never Come to Peace Again: Pontiac's Uprising and the Fate of the British Empire in North America |year = 2005 |work = [[University of Oklahoma Press]] |location = [[Norman, Oklahoma]] |edition = illustrated |isbn = 978-0-8061-3656-1 }}\n* {{cite book |last = Finley |first = Laura |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=d738P9jvNLsC&printsec=frontcover |title = Encyclopedia of School Crime and Violence |year = 2011 |publisher = [[ABC-CLIO]] |location = [[Santa Barbara, California]] |edition = 1st |isbn = 978-0-313-36239-2 |ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=ehzFBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover |title = School Violence: A Reference Handbook, 2nd Edition |year = 2014 |last = Finley |first = Laura |publisher = [[ABC-CLIO]] |location = [[Santa Barbara, California]] |edition = 2nd |isbn = 978-1-61069-624-1 |ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=qbUqS34F8l0C&printsec=frontcover |title = The Bully Society: School Shootings and the Crisis of Bullying in America's Schools |year = 2013 |last = Klein |first = Jessie |publisher = [[New York University Press]] |location = [[New York, New York]] |edition = reprint |isbn = 978-0-8147-6371-1 |ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=KZLCAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover |title = Books, Blackboards, and Bullets: School Shootings and Violence in America |year = 2008 |last = Lebrun |first = Marcel |publisher = [[Rowman & Littlefield]] Education |location = [[Lanham, Maryland]] |edition = 1st |isbn = 978-1-57886-904-6 |ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=2kHxdXe4CZ8C&printsec=frontcover |title = Pontiac's War: Its Causes, Course and Consequences |year = 2007 |last = Middleton |first = Richard |publisher = [[Routledge]] |location = [[New York City|New York]] |isbn = 978-0-415-97914-6 }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=eONxCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover |title = World Encyclopedia of 20th Century Murder |year = 1992 |last = Nash |first = Jay Robert |publisher = [[Rowman & Littlefield]] |edition = 1st |isbn = 978-1-59077-532-5 }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=YaLo1jgAorMC&printsec=frontcover |title = The Psychology and Law of Workplace Violence: A Handbook for Mental Health Professionals and Employers |year = 2004 |last1 = Perline |first1 = Irvin H. |last2 = Goldschmidt |first2 = Jona |publisher = Charles C Thomas Publisher |location = [[Springfield, Illinois]] |edition = illustrated |isbn = 978-0-398-07432-6 }}\n* {{cite book |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=MtY3RsRUjHYC&printsec=frontcover |title = Ending Campus Violence: New Approaches to Prevention |year = 2012 |last = Van Brunt |first = Brian |publisher = [[Routledge]] |isbn = 978-1-136-51494-4 }}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.in.gov/legislative/interim/committee/minutes/SSICG9O.pdf School Safety Interim Study Committee] \u2013 Indiana Legislative Services Agency (September 24, 2013)\n* [http://www.capenet.org/pdf/Outlook401.pdf Federal Report Looks at Crime and Safety in Schools] \u2013 Council for American Private Education (CAPE) (January 2015)\n* [http://nces.ed.gov/programs/crimeindicators/crimeindicators2014/ Indicators of School Crime and Safety: 2014] \u2013 [[National Center for Education Statistics]] (July 9, 2015)\n* [http://csgjusticecenter.org/youth/publications/indicators-of-school-crime-and-safety-2014/ Indicators of School Crime and Safety: 2014] \u2013 [[Council of State Governments]] Justice Center (July 15, 2015)\n* [http://cebcp.org/wp-content/Symposium2015/Robers.pdf Selected Findings from the Indicators of School Crime and Safety: 2014] \u2013 Center for Evidence-Based Crime Policy (CEBCP) Symposium (August 17, 2015)\n\n[[Category:Lists of disasters in the United States|School Shooting incidents.]]\n[[Category:School shootings in the United States|*]]\n[[Category:United States crime-related lists]]\n[[Category:Secondary education-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of school-related attacks|US]]\n", "name_user": "Greyjoy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_school_shootings_in_the_United_States"}
{"title_page": "Brandy Melville", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian  clothing brand}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name=IT'S ANOTHER BEAUTIFUL DAY TO BE ROGELIOOOOO\n|homepage= [http://brandymelville.com Official website]\n|industry=[[Retail]]\n|products=Apparel\n|foundation= {{Start date and age|1970}}\n|founder=Silvio Marsan\n|locations=95\n}}\n\n'''Brandy Melville''' is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[clothing]] and [[fashion]] accessories brand, marketing their products to teenage girls and young women. The company was established in 1970 in Italy by Silvio Marsan and his son, Stephan Marsan.<ref name=\"Brandy\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/unternehmen-und-konjunktur/Ich-bin-ein-BrandyGirl-/story/26797168|title=Ich bin ein Brandy-Girl|publisher=Tages-Anzeiger|date=January 4, 2015|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref> The brand name and logo was inspired by the fictional tale of two people \u2013 Brandy, an American girl, and Melville, an English guy who met in Rome and fell in love. \n\nBrandy Melville's first retail store was opened in 2009, bordering [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]] in the [[Westwood, Los Angeles|Westwood]] neighborhood of [[Los Angeles]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.racked.com/2014/9/24/7575693/brandy-melville|title=Smells Like Teen Spirit: Inside the Secretive World of Brandy Melville|date=September 24, 2014|publisher=Racked.com|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://dailybruin.com/2009/11/09/westwood-meets-italian-style/|title=New clothing store Brandy Melville brings Italian style straight to Westwood|date=September 24, 2014|publisher=Daily Bruin|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref> By 2015, the brand had grown to 95 stores worldwide. In a similar way to [[Primark]], the stores place little emphasis on advertising, relying instead on [[social media]] and word-of-mouth.<ref name=\"Brandy\"/> The clothing line is extended to some pop-up stores in Nordstrom and Pac Sun.\n\nThough the company originated in Europe, Brandy adjusts their prices, clothing styles, and accessory items to American customers by taking \"store style\" photos of the clothing worn by the customers shopping in-store. To keep a European [[Aesthetics|aesthetic]] within American stores, Brandy Melville marks the prices of clothing items with a fake \"euro\". One \"euro\" equals one American dollar.<ref name=\":1\" /> The company's products are sold in physical stores in places such as [[Europe]], the [[United States]], [[Asia]], [[Canada]], the [[United Kingdom]] and on their website. The biggest issue with Brandy Melville is how they only make their clothes in one size, which is not the case for some body types. The company in recent times has worked towards making different sized pants but keeps the shirts for the most part one size. They are intended to fit a UK size 4-6/ \n\nBrandy Melville has been described as trend-setting, relevant, cool and fast fashion.<ref name=\":0\" /> Brandy's one-size-fits-all aspect has brought criticism and controversy upon the company, with some customers unable to fit into the brand's clothing items, considering their size to be too big or small.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://college.usatoday.com/2014/04/04/brandy-melville-one-size-doesnt-always-fit-most/|title=Brandy Melville: One size doesn't always fit most|date=April 2014|accessdate=October 19, 2017|publisher=USA Today|first=Madison|last=Mills}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://observer.com/2015/07/these-one-size-fits-all-clothes-are-actually-size-zeroes/|title=These 'One-Size-Fits-All' Clothes Are Actually Size Zeroes|publisher=The Observer|date=July 7, 2015|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref> Most of Brandy's [[Clothing|apparel]] offers clothing in only one size except for some styles of jeans. Brandy's product research team consists of teenage employees starting at age 15 in an attempt to keep the company's styles contemporary.<ref name=\":0\" /> The company does not use usual advertising techniques they depend heavily on social media for their advertising. The Brandy Melville instagram account has 4 million followers. \n\nThe return policy states that clothing may be exchanged or returned for store credit within 14 days of purchase and all accessories and intimates are final sale.\n\n== Current operations and franchises ==\nBrandy Melville currently has 154 locations across the world - with 96 of those locations being in the US and 3 locations in Canada. Brandy Melville's huge success in the US did not reflect on their business in Canada. Over the past year Brandy Melville has closed 2 of their Toronto locations, Yorkdale mall <ref>{{Citation|title=Yorkdale Shopping Centre|date=2020-03-24|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Yorkdale_Shopping_Centre&oldid=947068800|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> and Square One <ref>{{Citation|title=Square One Shopping Centre|date=2020-03-03|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Square_One_Shopping_Centre&oldid=943631866|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>. As of now Brandy Melville makes around $125 million annually of sales and has a 20-25% growth rate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/9979e39e-08a1-11e7-97d1-5e720a26771b|title=Subscribe to read {{!}} Financial Times|website=www.ft.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Online operations ===\nCurrently Brandy Melville offers online shopping<ref>{{Citation|title=Online shopping|date=2020-02-28|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Online_shopping&oldid=943112557|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> to its customers in the United States however, shipping to Canada is still not available. Most of Brandy Melville's customers prefer online shopping due to customers not feeling comfortable or skinny enough to shop in stores because they do not fit their ideal \"girl\". \n\n==== Shops by country/region ====\nNumber of Brandy Melville locations in March 2020\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Country\n!No.\n|-\n|Hong Kong\n|1\n|-\n|Australia\n|1\n|-\n|Canada\n|3\n|-\n|Switzerland\n|15\n|-\n|Netherlands\n|2\n|-\n|Belgium\n|1\n|-\n|Spain\n|6\n|-\n|Germany\n|5\n|-\n|Italy\n|12\n|-\n|Great Britain\n|1\n|-\n|Portugal\n|2\n|-\n|France\n|3\n|-\n|Norway\n|1\n|-\n|Austria\n|1\n|-\n|UK\n|4\n|-\n|United States\n|96\n|}\n<br />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n[[Category:Fashion accessory brands]]\n[[Category:Clothing companies of Italy]]\n[[Category:Clothing companies established in 1970]]\n[[Category:1970 establishments in Switzerland]]\n\n\n{{Fashion-company-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian  clothing brand}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name=Brandy Melville\n|homepage= [http://brandymelville.com Official website]\n|industry=[[Retail]]\n|products=Apparel\n|foundation= {{Start date and age|1970}}\n|founder=Silvio Marsan\n|locations=95\n}}\n\n'''Brandy Melville''' is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[clothing]] and [[fashion]] accessories brand, marketing their products to teenage girls and young women. The company was established in 1970 in Italy by Silvio Marsan and his son, Stephan Marsan.<ref name=\"Brandy\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/unternehmen-und-konjunktur/Ich-bin-ein-BrandyGirl-/story/26797168|title=Ich bin ein Brandy-Girl|publisher=Tages-Anzeiger|date=January 4, 2015|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref> The brand name and logo was inspired by the fictional tale of two people \u2013 Brandy, an American girl, and Melville, an English guy who met in Rome and fell in love. \n\nBrandy Melville's first retail store was opened in 2009, bordering [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]] in the [[Westwood, Los Angeles|Westwood]] neighborhood of [[Los Angeles]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.racked.com/2014/9/24/7575693/brandy-melville|title=Smells Like Teen Spirit: Inside the Secretive World of Brandy Melville|date=September 24, 2014|publisher=Racked.com|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://dailybruin.com/2009/11/09/westwood-meets-italian-style/|title=New clothing store Brandy Melville brings Italian style straight to Westwood|date=September 24, 2014|publisher=Daily Bruin|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref> By 2015, the brand had grown to 95 stores worldwide. In a similar way to [[Primark]], the stores place little emphasis on advertising, relying instead on [[social media]] and word-of-mouth.<ref name=\"Brandy\"/> The clothing line is extended to some pop-up stores in Nordstrom and Pac Sun.\n\nThough the company originated in Europe, Brandy adjusts their prices, clothing styles, and accessory items to American customers by taking \"store style\" photos of the clothing worn by the customers shopping in-store. To keep a European [[Aesthetics|aesthetic]] within American stores, Brandy Melville marks the prices of clothing items with a fake \"euro\". One \"euro\" equals one American dollar.<ref name=\":1\" /> The company's products are sold in physical stores in places such as [[Europe]], the [[United States]], [[Asia]], [[Canada]], the [[United Kingdom]] and on their website. The biggest issue with Brandy Melville is how they only make their clothes in one size, which is not the case for some body types. The company in recent times has worked towards making different sized pants but keeps the shirts for the most part one size. They are intended to fit a UK size 4-6/ \n\nBrandy Melville has been described as trend-setting, relevant, cool and fast fashion.<ref name=\":0\" /> Brandy's one-size-fits-all aspect has brought criticism and controversy upon the company, with some customers unable to fit into the brand's clothing items, considering their size to be too big or small.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://college.usatoday.com/2014/04/04/brandy-melville-one-size-doesnt-always-fit-most/|title=Brandy Melville: One size doesn't always fit most|date=April 2014|accessdate=October 19, 2017|publisher=USA Today|first=Madison|last=Mills}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://observer.com/2015/07/these-one-size-fits-all-clothes-are-actually-size-zeroes/|title=These 'One-Size-Fits-All' Clothes Are Actually Size Zeroes|publisher=The Observer|date=July 7, 2015|accessdate=October 19, 2017}}</ref> Most of Brandy's [[Clothing|apparel]] offers clothing in only one size except for some styles of jeans. Brandy's product research team consists of teenage employees starting at age 15 in an attempt to keep the company's styles contemporary.<ref name=\":0\" /> The company does not use usual advertising techniques they depend heavily on social media for their advertising. The Brandy Melville instagram account has 4 million followers. \n\nThe return policy states that clothing may be exchanged or returned for store credit within 14 days of purchase and all accessories and intimates are final sale.\n\n== Current operations and franchises ==\nBrandy Melville currently has 154 locations across the world - with 96 of those locations being in the US and 3 locations in Canada. Brandy Melville's huge success in the US did not reflect on their business in Canada. Over the past year Brandy Melville has closed 2 of their Toronto locations, Yorkdale mall <ref>{{Citation|title=Yorkdale Shopping Centre|date=2020-03-24|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Yorkdale_Shopping_Centre&oldid=947068800|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> and Square One <ref>{{Citation|title=Square One Shopping Centre|date=2020-03-03|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Square_One_Shopping_Centre&oldid=943631866|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>. As of now Brandy Melville makes around $125 million annually of sales and has a 20-25% growth rate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/9979e39e-08a1-11e7-97d1-5e720a26771b|title=Subscribe to read {{!}} Financial Times|website=www.ft.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Online operations ===\nCurrently Brandy Melville offers online shopping<ref>{{Citation|title=Online shopping|date=2020-02-28|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Online_shopping&oldid=943112557|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> to its customers in the United States however, shipping to Canada is still not available. Most of Brandy Melville's customers prefer online shopping due to customers not feeling comfortable or skinny enough to shop in stores because they do not fit their ideal \"girl\". \n\n==== Shops by country/region ====\nNumber of Brandy Melville locations in March 2020\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Country\n!No.\n|-\n|Hong Kong\n|1\n|-\n|Australia\n|1\n|-\n|Canada\n|3\n|-\n|Switzerland\n|15\n|-\n|Netherlands\n|2\n|-\n|Belgium\n|1\n|-\n|Spain\n|6\n|-\n|Germany\n|5\n|-\n|Italy\n|12\n|-\n|Great Britain\n|1\n|-\n|Portugal\n|2\n|-\n|France\n|3\n|-\n|Norway\n|1\n|-\n|Austria\n|1\n|-\n|UK\n|4\n|-\n|United States\n|96\n|}\n<br />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n[[Category:Fashion accessory brands]]\n[[Category:Clothing companies of Italy]]\n[[Category:Clothing companies established in 1970]]\n[[Category:1970 establishments in Switzerland]]\n\n\n{{Fashion-company-stub}}\n", "name_user": "50.53.60.200", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandy_Melville"}
